    },
    {
      "name": "Candidates",
      "description": "API calls related to candidates and their answers.\n\nHot candidates: If you want the applicant to be marked by the system as a \"hot candidate,\"\ni.e., a candidate visible on the main page, attach the tag tag.hot to them. See more about hot candidates in Recruitis.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Comments",
      "description": "This section covers comments.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Checklists",
      "description": "This section covers API calls related to checklists linked to a candidate\u2019s answer. It is available only for companies that have checklists enabled.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Calendar",
      "description": "This section covers API calls related to calendars and reservation system.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Referrals",
      "description": "This section relates to referrals in the Recruitis system.\nThese referrals have access to their own section,\nfrom where they can share published job ads and thus help find new employees through the listed rewards.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Custom fields",
      "description": "API calls related to candidate custom fields.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Job filters",
      "description": "This is a specific area where we work with filters for particular job ads.\nOften, we want to filter job ads by information that the system does not provide out of the box,\nso we need to create these filters ourselves and assign them to the job ad.\nAfterward, we can filter by them.\n\nExample filters:\nHospital department (ICU, Gynecology, ENT, \u2026)\nTypes of operation (one-shift, two-shift, \u2026)\n\nA single job ad can have multiple filters assigned to it \u2014\nthis depends entirely on the recruiter creating the job ad.\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Files",
      "description": "This section allows file management, currently limited to downloading."
    },
    {
      "name": "Tasks",
      "description": "This section is used for listing tasks."
    },
    {
      "name": "Enumerations",
      "description": "Section responsible for returning various enumerations. \nPagination does not apply to any enumerations.\n    \n#### suitable_for parameter\n    \nThis parameter is included in the details of individual job ads. \nIf the parameter is not specified, it will not appear in the payload.\n    \n| ID  | Value                      |\n|-----|----------------------------|\n| 1   | Graduate                   |\n| 2   | Retired                    |\n| 3   | On parental leave          |\n| 4   | Unemployed                 |\n| 5   | Military service: NVS, ZVS |\n| 6   | Self-employed              |\n| 7   | Student                    |\n| 8   | Employed                   |\n| 10  | Not suitable for graduates |\n    \n#### remote_work parameter\n    \nThis parameter is included in the details of individual job ads. \nIf the parameter is not specified, it will not appear in the payload.\n    \n| Value   | Description                      |\n|---------|----------------------------------|\n| full    | 100% remote work allowed         |\n| partial | Partial remote work allowed      |\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Report",
      "description": "This section relates to data reporting from the Recruitis system."
    },
    {
      "name": "Webhooks",
      "description": "Recruitis can send information during system events using webhooks. \n\n### List\n\n| ID                          | Name                                             | Description                                                                 |\n|-----------------------------|--------------------------------------------------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| onAnswerAdd                 | Answer added to a job ad                         | Notification when a new answer to a job ad is created.                      |\n| onAnswerExported            | Candidate marked for export                      | Notification when a candidate is marked for export to an external system.   |\n| onAnswerFlowChange          | Candidate flow change                            | Notification when a candidate\u2019s flow is changed.                            |\n| onAnswerRejected            | Candidate rejected                               | Notification when a candidate is rejected.                                  |\n| onAnswerRemoved             | Candidate deleted                                | Notification when a candidate is deleted from the system.                   |\n| onChecklistItemStateUpdated | Checklist item state change                      | Notification when the state of a checklist item changes.                    |\n| onInterviewUpdated          | Interview accepted/rejected by candidate         | Notification when a candidate accepts or rejects an interview.              |\n| onOfferAdd                  | New job ad added                                 | Notification when a new job ad is added in the system.                      |\n| onOfferEdit                 | Job ad edited                                    | Notification when a job ad\u2019s content is changed.                            |\n| onOfferOpened               | Job ad opened                                    | Notification when a job ad\u2019s state changes to \"Open\".                       |\n| onOfferClosed               | Job ad closed                                    | Notification when a job ad\u2019s state changes to \"Closed\".                     |\n| onOfferArchived             | Job ad archived                                  | Notification when a job ad\u2019s state changes to \"Archived\".                   |\n| onOfferPublished            | Job ad published on a channel                    | Notification when a job ad is added to a publication channel.               |\n| onOfferUnpublished          | Job ad unpublished from a channel                | Notification when a job ad is removed from a publication channel.           |\n\n### Sample data\n\n```\n{\n    \"header\": {\n        \"id\": \"bc99fe9b69d65dac0757a2a98e07dab1\",\n        \"timestamp\": 1660288398,\n        \"entity_name\": \"job\",\n        \"entity_id\": 300300,\n        \"action\": \"add\",\n        \"signature\": \"466f53ef68a018757eb5665f0b201a3ac9e7ea8dc64632897413dcc50e89c8fc\"\n    },\n    \"body\": {\n        ...\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Response\n\nThe response must return HTTP 200. The response body can be anything; only the status code matters.\n\n#### Important:\n\nWhen adding a webhook, it is **MANDATORY** to first call the webhook [Domain Verification](#operation/verification).\n\n### Retries\n\nIf we receive a different HTTP code, the system will retry sending the webhook:\n- 1 \u2013 5 attempts every 1 minute\n- 6 \u2013 10 attempts every 5 minutes\n- 10 \u2013 15 attempts every 30 minutes\n- 16 \u2013 21 attempts every 90 minutes\n- 22nd attempt after 12 hours\n\nThe system retries for a total of 24 hours, after which the webhook is discarded.\n\n### Verification\n\nWebhooks are sent from the IP address ***82.208.7.212***, we recommend whitelisting this IP.  \nAdditionally, the data in the header is signed so that it can be trusted. \n\n### Example of signature creation in PHP\n\n```\n$secret = 'this-value-is-shared-through-another-channel';\n$sig = hash('sha256', '$id|$timestamp|$entity_name|$entity_id|$action|$secret');\n```\n"
    },
    {
      "name": "Changelog",
      "description": "<!--TODO: Changelog -->\n\n* **18.11.2025: branch v1 `1.14.1`**\n    * New tasks endpoint (`GET /tasks/table`) implemented, the older one got deprecated.\n\n* **2.9.2025: branch v1 `1.14.0`**\n    * The entire documentation has been translated into English to meet everyone\u2019s needs.\n\n* **16.10.2024: branch v1 `1.13.1`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `PATCH /answer/{answer_id}`. Toto vol\u00e1n\u00ed se vztahuje k zam\u00edtnut\u00ed adpov\u011bdi a p\u0159\u00edpadn\u00e9mu vr\u00e1cen\u00ed zam\u00edtnut\u00e9 odpov\u011bdi zp\u011bt do aktivn\u00edch.\n\n* **30.4.2024: branch v1 `1.13.0`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1na vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET` a`PUT` na adres\u00e1ch `/answers/{answer_id}/extra` a `/candidates/{user_id}/extra`. Tato vol\u00e1n\u00ed se vztahuj\u00ed k pr\u00e1ci se \u0161t\u00edtky.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /activity_feed`, kter\u00e9 vrac\u00ed historii akc\u00ed zadan\u00e9ho kandid\u00e1ta.\n\n* **8.4.2024: branch v1 `1.12.9`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` a `GET /jobs/{id}` p\u0159id\u00e1n query parametr `with_automation`, kter\u00fd umo\u017e\u0148uje vypsat ve v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed tak\u00e9 nov\u00e9 pole `automations`.\n    * Nov\u011b vrac\u00ed vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` a `GET /jobs/{id}` ve v\u00fdpisu tak\u00e9 nov\u00e9 pole `sharing`.\n\n* **31.1.2024: branch v1 `1.12.8`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` p\u0159id\u00e1n nepovinn\u00fd parametr `text_language`, kter\u00fd umo\u017e\u0148uje filtrovat podle jazyku inzer\u00e1tu.\n\n* **28.11.2023: branch v1 `1.12.7`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1na nov\u00e1 sekce Comments, kter\u00e1 obsluhuje pr\u00e1ci s pozn\u00e1mkami, s vol\u00e1n\u00edmi `GET /comments`, `POST /comments`, `PUT /comments`, `DELETE /comments`.\n\n* **2.8.2023: branch v1 `1.12.6`**\n    * Vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/workfields` a `GET /enums/workfields/` (d\u0159\u00edve byla kv\u016fli dokumentaci pomocn\u011b rozd\u011blena do dvou podobn\u00fdch) byla spojena do jednoho vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/workfields`.\n\n* **17.7.2023: branch v1 `1.12.5`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1na vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs/{id}/form`, `GET /jobs/{id}/form/validate` a `GET /candidates/form/{id}`, kter\u00e1 se t\u00fdkaj\u00ed odpov\u011bdn\u00edch formul\u00e1\u0159\u016f.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1n webhook \"P\u0159ijet\u00ed / Odm\u00edtnut\u00ed pohovoru ze strany kandid\u00e1ta\".\n    * Do sekce Calendar p\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `DELETE /calendar/reservation-links/{id}`, kter\u00e9 ma\u017ee rezerva\u010dn\u00ed odkazy.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /reports` u parametru `lists[]` p\u0159id\u00e1na mo\u017enost `custom-fields`.\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /reports` p\u0159id\u00e1n atribut `custom-fields`, s d\u00edl\u010d\u00edmi atributy `ID`, `Name`, `Label`, `Value`, `Type`, `AnswerID`, `UserID`.\n\n* **5.6.2023: branch v1 `1.12.4`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1na nov\u00e1 sekce Calendar s vol\u00e1n\u00edmi `GET /calendar/reservation-links`, `POST /calendar/reservation-links` a `GET /calendar/interviews/{answer_id}`.\n\n* **25.5.2023: branch v1 `1.12.3`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1n webhook \"Zm\u011bna stavu polo\u017eky checklistu\".\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /candidates` p\u0159id\u00e1n atribut `email`.\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /answers` p\u0159id\u00e1ny atributy `user_id` a `user_email`.\n\n* **10.5.2023: branch v1 `1.12.2`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1na nov\u00e1 sekce Checklists s vol\u00e1n\u00edmi `GET /answers/{answer_id}/checklists/{flow_id}` a `PUT /checklists/{answer_id}/item/{item_id}/state`. Tato sekce se vztahuje pouze ke spole\u010dnostem, kter\u00e9 maj\u00ed checklisty povolen\u00e9.\n\n* **18.4.2023: branch v1 `1.12.1`**\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /reports` u atributu `Answers` p\u0159id\u00e1ny atributy `Salary` a `HiringProposal`. Oba s d\u00edl\u010d\u00edmi atributy `Amount`,`Currency`,`Unit`,`Type`.\n\n* **11.4.2023: branch v1 `1.12.0`**\n    * Atribut `office_id` v detailech pozice ozna\u010den jako deprecated. `office_id` pobo\u010dky p\u0159i\u0159azen\u00e9 k inzer\u00e1tu ud\u00e1v\u00e1 `office_id` v atributu `addresses` v kombinaci s `is_primary=true`.\n    * Do parametru `extra` p\u0159id\u00e1n d\u00edl\u010d\u00ed parametr `answer_tag`.\n\n* **13.3.2023: branch v1 `1.11.9`**\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /tasks` p\u0159id\u00e1n atribut `job` s d\u00edl\u010d\u00edmi atributy `id` a `title`.\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` a `GET /jobs/id` do atributu salary p\u0159id\u00e1ny atributy `is_range`, `is_min_visible`, `is_max_visible` a byl zm\u011bn\u011bn parametr visible, kter\u00fd nov\u011b nab\u00fdv\u00e1 hodnoty true pokud: (is_range && is_min_visible) || is_max_visible.\n\n* **6.3.2023: branch v1 `1.11.8`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/flows`.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /answers` p\u0159id\u00e1n nepovinn\u00fd parametr `salary` (Po\u017eadovan\u00fd plat).\n\n* **11.1.2023: branch v1 `1.11.7`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `PUT /jobs/{id}/access` p\u0159ejmenov\u00e1n parametr `referrer` na `referer`. Vol\u00e1n\u00ed bude zat\u00edm fungovat s ob\u011bma variantami.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `PUT /jobs/{id}/access` p\u0159id\u00e1n nepovinn\u00fd parametr `referral`.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed PUT `/logout`.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1n webhook \"Verifikace Dom\u00e9ny\".\n\n\n* **20.12.2022: branch v1 `1.11.6`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` p\u0159id\u00e1n parametr `order_by`, kter\u00fd nab\u00fdv\u00e1 hodnot `date_created` nebo `date_channel_assigned`.\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` a `GET /jobs/{id}` v atributu `channels` p\u0159id\u00e1n d\u00edl\u010d\u00ed atribut `date_assigned`.\n\n\n* **3.11.2022: branch v1 `1.11.5`**\n    * Aktualizov\u00e1ny v\u00fdsledky v\u0161ech `GET` vol\u00e1n\u00ed.\n\n\n* **27.10.2022: branch v1 `1.11.4`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /tasks`.\n\n\n* **25.10.2022: branch v1 `1.11.3`**\n    * Aktualizace vyhled\u00e1v\u00e1n\u00ed: `GET /referrals/?search={\"external_id\" : \"9D96W3-66D2\"}`.\n    Search parametr byl upraven tak, \u017ee p\u016fvodn\u00ed funcionalita byla zachov\u00e1na (search=nejakystring), nicm\u00e9n\u011b takto vyhled\u00e1v\u00e1 nap\u0159\u00ed\u010d v\u0161emi atributy (email,phone,name,external_id).\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/reject_reasons`.\n\n\n* **20.10.2022: branch v1 `1.11.2`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /answers/{answer_id}/interviews/notes` - z\u00edsk\u00e1n\u00ed v\u0161ech pohovor\u016f k odpov\u011bdi.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /answers/{answer_id}` p\u0159ibyl parametr `view`, kter\u00fd nab\u00fdv\u00e1 hodnot `basic` nebo `extended`.\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /answers/{answer_id}` p\u0159d\u00e1ny atributy `flow_history` a `requirements`.\n\n\n* **19.10.2022: branch v1 `1.11.1`** \n    * P\u0159\u00edd\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /jobs/{id}/recommend/applicant`.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` p\u0159id\u00e1n parametr `with_rewards`.\n\n\n* **18.10.2022: branch v1 `1.11.0`** \n    * P\u0159\u00edd\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /customfields/user/{userid}`.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /customfields/user/{userid}/{answerid}`.\n    \n\n* **26.9.2022: branch v1 `1.10.0`** \n    * P\u0159\u00edd\u00e1n\u00ed webhook\u016f do dokumentace.\n\n\n* **9.3.2022: branch v1 `1.9.0`**\n    * V dokumentaci jsou nyn\u00ed pops\u00e1ny nov\u00e9 opr\u00e1vn\u011bn\u00ed token\u016f.\n    * Bylo odstran\u011bno deprecated vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET enums/filters`.\n\n\n* **9.2.2022: branch v1 `1.8.4`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1ny parametry `suitable_for` a `remote_work` do v\u00fdpisu inzer\u00e1t\u016f. Viz [Enumerations](#tag/Enumerations) sekce.\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET answer/` a `GET answers/` je nyn\u00ed atribut `reject_reason` - d\u016fvod zam\u00edtnut\u00ed kandid\u00e1ta.\n\n\n* **2.2.2022: branch v1 `1.8.3`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `PUT jobs/access/id`.\n\n\n* **10.1.2022: branch v1 `1.8.2`**\n    * P\u0159ibyl object `contact - employee` v `GET jobs/` vol\u00e1n\u00ed.\n\n\n* **25.11.2021: branch v1 `1.8.1`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` p\u0159ibyl parametr `fte`.\n\n\n* **16.11.2021: branch v1 `1.8.0`**\n    * P\u0159ibyl popis firemn\u00edho typu tokenu v\u010d. v\u0161ech kompatibiln\u00edch API vol\u00e1n\u00ed.\n    * Vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET enums/...` je nyn\u00ed mo\u017en\u00e9 s firemn\u00edm tokenem.\n    * Vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET filters/...` je nyn\u00ed mo\u017en\u00e9 s firemn\u00edm tokenem.\n    * Vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET a POST candidates/communications` vy\u017eaduje nyn\u00ed `full_access` token.\n\n\n* **20.5.2021: branch v1 `1.7.5`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` p\u0159ibyl parametr `office_id` v `addresses`.\n    * Odstran\u011bn\u00ed deprecated parametr\u016f bylo posunuto na 1.9.2021.\n\n\n* **25.1.2021: branch v1 `1.7.4`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST answers/` p\u0159ibyl parametr `send_notification`.\n    * Odstran\u011bn\u00ed deprecated parametr\u016f bylo posunuto na 1.4.2021.\n\n\n* **12.11.2020: branch v1 `1.7.3`**\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` je nyn\u00ed atribut `text_language`.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST jobs/` p\u0159ibyl parametr `text_language`.\n    * Odstran\u011bn\u00ed deprecated parametr\u016f bylo posunuto na 16.12.2020.\n\n\n* **22.9.2020: branch v1 `1.7.2`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/employments`, kter\u00e9 vrac\u00ed n\u00e1zvy typ\u016f pracovn\u00edch pom\u011br\u016f a jejich ID.\n\n\n* **15.9.2020: branch v1 `1.7.1`**\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` je nyn\u00ed lep\u00e9 pops\u00e1n atribut `active`, viz p\u0159ehled parametr\u016f [zde](#tag/Jobs/paths/~1jobs/get).\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET reports/` p\u0159ibyl parametr `closed_duration` a `date_closed`. Parametr `date_end` byl ozna\u010den jako deprecated a bude 16.11.2020 odstran\u011bn.\n\n\n* **5.9.2020: branch v1 `1.7.0`**\n    * U v\u00fdsledku vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` byly p\u0159id\u00e1ny tyto atributy: `date_closed`,`access_state`,`closed_duration`,`activity_state`.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` byly p\u0159id\u00e1ny tyto request parametry: `activity_state`,`access_state`.\n    * `activity_state` Je synonymum pro nyn\u011bj\u0161\u00ed parametr `status` obsahuj\u00edc\u00ed aktivn\u00ed a neaktivn\u00ed inzer\u00e1ty. Smazan\u00e9 inzr\u00e1ty jsou nyni ozna\u010den\u00e9 jako archivovan\u00e9 a p\u0159esunuty pod parametr `access_state` s hodnotou 3.\n    * `access_state` Je request parametr filtruj\u00edc\u00ed otev\u0159en\u00e9, uzav\u0159en\u00e9, archivovan\u00e9 pozice, drafty a \u0161ablony.\n    * Podrobn\u011bj\u0161\u00ed popis naleznete v p\u0159ehledu parametr\u016f [zde](#tag/Jobs/paths/~1jobs/get).\n\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` jsou tyto parametry ozna\u010deny jako deprecated a v budoucnu dojde k jejim vymaz\u00e1n\u00ed:\n    * `source_site`: Prvek byl zav\u00e1d\u011bj\u00edc\u00ed.\n    * `date_end`: Bude nahrazen argumentem `date_closed`. D\u016fvodem je p\u0159esn\u011bj\u0161\u00ed pojmenov\u00e1n\u00ed parametru, kter\u00e9 zna\u010d\u00ed datum uzav\u0159en\u00ed pozice.\n    * `only_deleted`: Vr\u00e1tit smazan\u00e9 (resp. archivovan\u00e9 pozice) bude mo\u017en\u00e9 p\u0159es parametr `access_state` s hodnotou 3.\n    * `include_inactive`: Neaktivn\u00ed pozice (tj. pozice, kter\u00e9 nejsou aktivn\u00ed na \u017e\u00e1dn\u00e9m pulika\u010dn\u00edm kan\u00e1lu)  se daj\u00ed vr\u00e1tit p\u0159es parametr `activity_state` s hodnotou 2, pop\u0159. 3 (bitmapa).\n    * `status` s hodnotou 4 (drafty) se nyn\u00ed m\u00e1 volat p\u0159es parametr `access_state` s hodnotou 4.\n    * `status` s hodnotou 8 (smazan\u00e9) se nyn\u00ed m\u00e1 volat p\u0159es parametr `access_state` s hodnotou 3.\n\n    * **Toerie:** Jedn\u00e1 se o zjednodu\u0161en\u00ed filtra\u010dn\u00edch mo\u017enost\u00ed pozic se zachov\u00e1n\u00edm v\u0161ech mo\u017en\u00fdch st\u00e1vaj\u00edc\u00edch variant. Z\u00e1rove\u0148 bylo pot\u0159eba zakomponovat novou logiku otev\u0159en\u00fdch a uzav\u0159en\u00fdch pozic.\n\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST answers/` nelze p\u0159idat odpov\u011b\u010f v p\u0159\u00edpad\u011b, \u017ee sm\u011bruje na archivovanou pozici. Tento po\u017eadavek vrac\u00ed `code` `api.error.job.wrong_acess_type`.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1n chybov\u00fd k\u00f3d `api.error.job.disallowed_acess_type`.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no API vol\u00e1n\u00ed `PUT jobs/(id)/access_state/(state)` pro vytvo\u0159en\u00ed zm\u011bnu uzav\u00edr\u00e1n\u00ed / otev\u00edr\u00e1n\u00ed a archivaci pozic.\n\n    * **Pozor: 16.12.2020 Dojde k t\u011bmto zm\u011bn\u00e1m:**\n    * Ve v\u00fdpisu inzer\u00e1t\u016f (`GET jobs/` a `GET jobs/id`) dojde k p\u0159ejmenov\u00e1n\u00ed parametru `date_end` na `date_closed` (P\u016fvodn\u00ed parametr `date_end` ji\u017e nebude dostupn\u00fd.), takt\u00e9\u017e se odstran\u00ed request parametr `only_deleted` a `include_inactive`.\n    * Ve v\u00fdpisu inzer\u00e1t\u016f (`GET jobs/` a `GET jobs/id`) dojde k odstran\u011bn\u00ed filtrovac\u00edch request parametr\u016f  `only_deleted` a `include_inactive`.\n    * Ve v\u00fdpisu inzer\u00e1t\u016f (`GET jobs/` a `GET jobs/id`) dojde k p\u0159ejmenov\u00e1n\u00ed filtrovac\u00ed polo\u017eky `status` na `activity_state` s bitmap hodnotami 1 a 2, viz p\u0159ehled parametr\u016f [zde](#tag/Jobs/paths/~1jobs/get).\n    * Ve v\u00fdpisu reportu (`GET reports/` ) dojde k odstran\u011bn\u00ed polo\u017eky `date_end`.\n    * pozn.: Do tohoto datumu bude dostupn\u00fd ve\u0161ker\u00fd star\u00fd i nov\u00fd obsah.\n\n\n* **19.8.2020: branch v1 `1.6.1`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` A `GET jobs/id` jsou v odpov\u011bdi nav\u00edc tyto parametry: `public_id`,`salary`,`education`,`last_update`,`draft`. Byl roz\u0161\u00edren parametr `details` o `facebook_picture_path` a `opening_reason`\n\n\n* **1.6.2020: branch v1 `1.6.0`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no API pro vytvo\u0159en\u00ed report\u016f ze syst\u00e9mu.\n    * P\u0159ibyla dokumentace na zobrazov\u00e1n\u00ed konkr\u00e9tn\u00ed odpov\u011bdi (`GET answers/id`).\n    * U dotazu na seznam odpov\u011bd\u00ed nyn\u00ed vrac\u00edme parametr `hash` v konkr\u00e9tn\u00ed p\u0159\u00edloze.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET answers/id` je mo\u017en\u00e9 volat parametr `im_author`.\n\n\n* **19.2.2020: branch v1 `1.5.0`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no API pro vytv\u00e1\u0159en\u00ed komunikace s uchaze\u010dem.\n    * U API s komunikac\u00ed s uchaze\u010dem se nyn\u00ed vypisuj\u00ed detailn\u011bji valida\u010dn\u00ed chyby (`meta`.`errors`). Postupn\u011b bude hl\u00e1\u0161en\u00ed o chyb\u00e1ch ve validaci ve v\u0161ech vol\u00e1n\u00ed.\n\n\n* **14.1.2020: branch v1 `1.4.2`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET jobs/` je mo\u017en\u00e9 volat parametr `status` a filtrovat s n\u00edm i draft inzer\u00e1ty.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST jobs/` kter\u00e9 um\u00ed vytvo\u0159it draft inzer\u00e1t. (n\u00e1sledn\u011b je ho mo\u017en\u00e9 dokon\u010dit v Recruitisu)\n\n\n* **15.7.2019: branch v1 `1.4.1`**\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET files/` je mo\u017en\u00e9 volat parametr `hash` jako pole. Sou\u010det v\u0161ech p\u0159\u00edloh mus\u00ed b\u00fdt men\u0161\u00ed, ne\u017e 30MB.\n    * Do dokumentace byl p\u0159id\u00e1n popis s meta.code `api.error.response.too_big`.\n    * Do seznamu odpov\u011bd\u00ed p\u0159ibyly parametry odpov\u011bdi `job_contact_name`,`job_contact_email`,`job_contact_phone`\n\n\n* **11.7.2019: branch v1 `1.4`**\n    * P\u0159ibyla dokumentace na zobrazov\u00e1n\u00ed seznamu odpov\u011bd\u00ed (`GET answers/`).\n    * P\u0159ibyla dokumentace na stahov\u00e1n\u00ed p\u0159\u00edloh (`GET files/`).\n\n\n* **3.12.2018: branch v1 `1.3.4`**\n    * V dokumentaci p\u0159ibyl popis stavu p\u0159i nedostupnosti API.\n    * P\u0159ibyly nov\u00e9 k\u00f3dy chyb: `api.error.system.unavailable`, `api.error.request.property.wrong_text_length`,`api.error.request.property.maximum_array_items`\n\n\n* **22.10.2018: branch v1 `1.3.3`**\n    * Byla p\u0159id\u00e1na nov\u00e1 sekce `referrals`, ve kter\u00e9 je vol\u00e1n\u00ed na p\u0159id\u00e1n\u00ed a v\u00fdpis referral\u016f.\n\n\n* **16.10.2018: branch v1 `1.3.2`**\n    * Do odpov\u011bdi u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` p\u0159ibyl nov\u00fd prvek `employment` a `education`.\n\n\n* **Pozor: 18.9.2018 p\u0159ijde zm\u011bna ve vol\u00e1n\u00ed konkr\u00e9tn\u00edho inzer\u00e1tu (`GET /jobs/id`): Nebude se nad\u00e1le vracet pole s jedn\u00edm inzer\u00e1tem, ale bude vracet p\u0159\u00edmo objekt s dan\u00fdm inzer\u00e1tem. P\u0159ipravte na to pros\u00edm svoje aplikace.**\n\n\n* **17.9.2018: branch v1 `1.3.1`**\n    * Bylo p\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `DELETE /candidates`.\n    * P\u0159ibyl popis kv\u00f3t.\n    * P\u0159ibyla kv\u00f3ta `quota_candidates_delete`.\n\n\n* **11.9.2018: branch v1 `1.3`**\n    * Bylo p\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /candidates`.\n    * Do dokumentace byl p\u0159id\u00e1n popis tag\u016f.\n    * Validace telefonn\u00edho kontaktu v requestu `POST /answers` nyn\u00ed akceptuje spr\u00e1vn\u00e9 \u010desk\u00e9 form\u00e1ty.\n    * Validace emailu v requestu `POST /answers` nyn\u00ed akceptuje znak \"+\".\n\n\n* **6.9.2018: branch v1 `1.2.3`**\n    * Do vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` p\u0159ibyl parametr `include_inactive`.\n    * Do vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` p\u0159ibyl parametr `include_inactive`.\n    * Vol\u00e1n\u00ed u neexistuj\u00edc\u00edho inzer\u00e1tu (`GET /jobs/id`) kon\u010d\u00ed s http_statusem `404` nam\u00edsto pr\u00e1zdn\u00e9 `200` odpov\u011bdi.\n    * Aktualizace dokumentace o n\u011bkter\u00e9 d\u016fle\u017eit\u00e9 informace (popis jednotliv\u00fdch atribut\u016f u inzer\u00e1tu).\n\n\n* **5.9.2018: branch v1 `1.2.2`**\n    * Do odpov\u011bdi u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /Answers` p\u0159ibyl parametr `source`.\n    * Do odpov\u011bdi u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs` p\u0159ibyl parametr `details`.\n    * Server nyn\u00ed vrac\u00ed p\u0159esn\u011bj\u0161\u00ed informace u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs`, dle specifikace dokumentace.\n    * Aktualizace dokumentace o n\u011bkter\u00e9 d\u016fle\u017eit\u00e9 informace.\n\n\n* **28.8.2018: branch v1 `1.2.1`**\n    * Do odpov\u011bdi u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /Answers` p\u0159ibyly nov\u00e9 mo\u017enosti (p\u0159id\u00e1n\u00ed odkaz\u016f na soci\u00e1ln\u00ed s\u00edt\u011b uchaze\u010de).\n    * Do odpov\u011bdi vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /Answers` p\u0159ibyl parametr `date_created` v objektu `gdpr_agreement`.\n\n\n* **6.8.2018: branch v1 `1.2`**\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1na sekce **Filters**\n    * Zprovozn\u011bn parametr filter_id u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs`.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /answer`  p\u0159ibyl parametr `referral_id`, `channel_id` a `extra`, kter\u00fd dovoluje p\u0159idat k odpov\u011bdi pozn\u00e1mku nebo tag..\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /answer`  byl zprovozn\u011bn parametr `channel_id`.\n    * U vol\u00e1n\u00ed `POST /answer`  byl upraven parametr `gppr_agreements` - nyn\u00ed je roz\u0161\u00ed\u0159en o dal\u0161\u00ed atributy.\n    * Vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/filters` je ozna\u010deno jako deprecated. Nam\u00edsto toho se doporu\u010duje volat `GET /filters`.\n\n\n* **19.7.2018: branch v1 `1.1.1`**\n    * Zprovozn\u011bn parametr channel_id u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /jobs`.\n    * Do odpov\u011bdi `GET /jobs` p\u0159ibyly tyto polo\u017eky: `description` a `workfields`.\n    * Opraven parametr channel_assignation u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/workfields`.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vynucen\u00ed spr\u00e1vn\u00fdch typ\u016f token\u016f u vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/workfields` a `GET /jobs`.\n    * Standardizov\u00e1ny n\u011bkter\u00e9 k\u00f3dov\u00e9 ozna\u010den\u00ed chyb + jsou zve\u0159ejn\u011bny a pops\u00e1ny v dokumentaci.\n    * V dokumentaci jsou p\u0159ips\u00e1ny dal\u0161\u00ed dodate\u010dn\u00e9 informace o API.\n\n\n* **9.7.2018: branch v1 `1.1`**\n    * Zprovozn\u011bno vol\u00e1n\u00ed nad re\u00e1ln\u00fdmi daty na url adrese: `https://app.recruitis.io/api2/`.\n    * `GET /jobs` odstran\u011bn parametr `regions`. Nam\u00edsto n\u011bho se bude vyu\u017e\u00edvat parametr `office_id`. Filtrace podle lokality nen\u00ed v nejbli\u017e\u0161\u00edm pl\u00e1nu v\u00fdvoje.\n    * `GET /jobs` parametr `workfields` p\u0159ejmenov\u00e1n na `workfield_id` (zp\u011btn\u00e1 kompatibilita je zachov\u00e1na).\n    * `GET /jobs` p\u0159id\u00e1n parametr `office_id`.\n    * P\u0159id\u00e1no vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enums/offices`.\n    * Vol\u00e1n\u00ed `GET /enum/*` p\u0159ejmenov\u00e1no na `GET /enums/*`(zp\u011btn\u00e1 kompatibilita je zachov\u00e1na: st\u00e1le se d\u00e1 volat `enums`).\n    * Zprovozn\u011bno vol\u00e1n\u00ed na `https://api.recruitis.io/`(vol\u00e1n\u00ed na https://app.recruitis.io/api2/ bude zachov\u00e1no).\n\n\n* **18.6.2018: branch v1 `1.0.1`**\n    * `POST /Answers` nyn\u00ed p\u0159ij\u00edm\u00e1 parametr `attachment` `base64`. V t\u00e9to n\u00e1vaznosti je nyn\u00ed povinn\u00fd atribut `attachment` `filename`.\n\n\n* **4.5.2018: branch v1 `1.0.0`**\n    * Ust\u00e1len\u00e1 verze API vol\u00e1n\u00ed `jobs` , `answers` a `login`.\n    * Po\u010d\u00e1te\u010dn\u00ed verze.\n"
    }
  ],
  "paths": {
    "/login": {
      "put": {
        "tags": [
          "Authentication"
        ],
        "summary": "Log in",
        "description": "Endpoint for generating a Bearer token for a user. The default response is 200.\n\n- `device_id` is an ID generated by Google Inc.'s Firebase service. If the system receives this parameter,\nit allows sending SMS messages through this login and assumes it is a mobile application.\n- `device_name` is only a label for the given API connection. Under this name, the user will see it in Recruitis. Once\nthe device_name is recorded, it cannot be changed via an API call.\n\nThis function does not need to be called if you already have a generated token. **This function returns a token with the `full_access` property.**\n\n#### Requirements\n\n* No authorization required.\n",
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                  "password": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "password"
                  },
                  "username": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "format": "email",
                    "example": "user@test.cz"
                  },
                  "device_id": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "s6g4g6d35hsf642s"
                  },
                  "device_name": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "Samsung S25"
                  }
                },
                "required": [
                  "password",
                  "username"
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "security": [],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "The login was successful.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "payload": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "token": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "30bcaf299e100318906fef2f442505216fa28af1.11196.99382ec77e2a79ac2af2671730817ec6"
                        },
                        "device_id": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "s6g4g6d35hsf642s"
                        },
                        "device_name": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "Samsung S25"
                        }
                      }
                    },
                    "meta": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "code": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "api.ok"
                        },
                        "duration": {
                          "type": "integer",
                          "example": 60
                        },
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "OK"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Response401"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/logout": {
      "put": {
        "tags": [
          "Authentication"
        ],
        "summary": "Log out",
        "description": "This call sends the currently used token and sets it to the state `disabled=1`.\nFurther calls with this token will return an error until a new login is performed.\n\n#### Requirements\n\n* The call must include an authorization token.\n* Compatible with the company token.\n* Token types: `full_access`, `public_access`\n* Does not support the new token type.\n",
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "The logout was successful.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "payload": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "nullable": true,
                      "example": null
                    },
                    "meta": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "code": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "api.ok"
                        },
                        "duration": {
                          "type": "integer",
                          "example": 60
                        },
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "Account has been logged off."
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Response401"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/me": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Me"
        ],
        "summary": "Get my information",
        "description": "Retrieve information about the currently logged-in account.\n\n#### Requirements\n\n* The call must include an authorization token.\n* Compatible with the company token.\n* New token type:\n    * The token must have the `api.device.read` permission.\n    \n",
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "The data has been found.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "payload": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "token_id": {
                          "type": "integer"
                        },
                        "employee_id": {
                          "type": "integer"
                        },
                        "company_id": {
                          "type": "integer"
                        },
                        "device_id": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "device_name": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "fullname": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "initials": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "email": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "format": "email"
                        },
                        "company_name": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "nullable": true
                        },
                        "avatar": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "token_type": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "account_role": {
                          "type": "string"
                        },
                        "token_date_expiration": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "format": "date-time",
                          "description": "Format YYYY-mm-dd HH:mm:ss",
                          "nullable": true
                        },
                        "quotas": {
                          "type": "object",
                          "properties": {
                            "daily_quota_candidates_delete": {
                              "type": "integer"
                            }
                          }
                        },
                        "extra": {
                          "type": "array",
                          "items": {
                            "type": "object"
                          }
                        },
                        "login_id": {
                          "type": "integer"
                        },
                        "is_company": {
                          "type": "boolean"
                        },
                        "person_id": {
                          "type": "integer"
                        }
                      },
                      "example": {
                        "token_id": 21650,
                        "employee_id": 27123,
                        "company_id": 11,
                        "device_id": "gsjfg35sfg4",
                        "device_name": "Samsung S20",
                        "fullname": "Tester Cypress",
                        "initials": "TC",
                        "email": "test@test.test",
                        "company_name": "Recruitis.io",
                        "avatar": "http://avatar.url.cz/avatar/avatar_2.jpg",
                        "token_type": "full_access",
                        "account_role": "admin",
                        "token_date_expiration": null,
                        "quotas": {
                          "daily_quota_candidates_delete": 0
                        },
                        "extra": [],
                        "login_id": 134568,
                        "is_company": false,
                        "person_id": 954305
                      }
                    },
                    "meta": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "code": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "api.ok"
                        },
                        "duration": {
                          "type": "integer",
                          "example": 90
                        },
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "OK"
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "401": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Response401"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/jobs": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Jobs"
        ],
        "summary": "Get all jobs",
        "description": "Retrieves all job advertisements. They can be filtered by fields (professions), filters, and distribution channels. \n\nIf no job advertisements are returned, HTTP status `200` is returned with meta code `api.response.null`.\n\n#### Requirements\n\n* The call must include an authorization token.\n* Compatible with the company token.\n* New token type:\n    * The token must have the `api.position.read` permission.\n* Old token types:\n    * Token type: `public_access`: if it is a public job ad (published on company websites, XML, or job portals) \u2013 determined by `channel_id`.\n    * Token type: `full_access`: if it is an internal job ad \u2013 determined by `channel_id`.\n\nTip: If you want to filter by addresses, you can assign job ads in Recruitis to specific branches \nand then filter by them (branches return addresses, and under one address you can include multiple branches).\n\n#### Parameter activity_state\n\nThe parameter filters positions based on whether they are active or inactive.  \nAt the same time, the parameter is a bitmask, so individual values can be summed and used together \n(enables filtering by multiple options at once).\n\n| Parameter        | Value | Note                                                         |\n|------------------|-------|--------------------------------------------------------------|\n| Active position  | 1     | A position that is present in at least one publication channel. |\n| Inactive position| 2     | A position that is not present in any publication channel.      |\n\n\n#### Parameter access_state\n\nThe parameter filters job ads based on the logic of open and closed positions.  \nUnlike `activity_state`, individual values **cannot** be combined.\n\n| Parameter        | Value | Note                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                |\n|------------------|-------|-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| Open position    | 1     | An open position is present in at least one publication channel. Applications can be submitted to it, and it is the only one that does not require a `full_access` token.                                                                           |\n| Closed position  | 2     | A closed position is not present in any publication channel but can still receive applications.                                                                                                                                                     |\n| Archived position| 3     | An archived position (previously deleted) is a position intended for reopening or permanent deletion. It does not accept new applications and does not allow editing of existing ones. Archiving anonymizes candidates without GDPR consent. Returns only a list of position IDs. |\n| Draft            | 4     | A draft position of the currently logged-in recruiter.                                                                                                                                                                                               |\n| Template         | 5     | A position designated as a template. It can belong either to the currently logged-in recruiter or to the entire company.                                                                                                                             |\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "limit",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The maximum limit for the paginator is 50. If not specified, it returns 10 items.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "default": 10,
              "maximum": 50
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "page",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Current page.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "default": 1
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "with_automation",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "If with_automation=1 is specified, the result of the call will also include a new field automations.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "text_language",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Parameter filters by language.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": [
                "cs",
                "sk",
                "en",
                "de",
                "ro",
                "bg",
                "hu",
                "pl"
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "workfield_id[]",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filtering by field (profession) IDs. See more in [Enumerations - Workfields](#tag/Enumerations/paths/~1enums~1workfields/get).\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "office_id[]",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filters by branch IDs.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "filter_id[]",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filtering by IDs of individual filter items assigned to the job ad. See more in [Job Filters](#tag/Job-filters/paths/~1filters/get).\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "channel_id[]",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Restriction to specific channels. More information about channels is returned by the enumeration, see [Enumerations - Company channels](#tag/Enumerations/paths/~1enums~1channels/get).\nIf the parameter is specified, the array will be returned sorted by the date of assignment to the channel. If the parameter is not specified, all possible job ads will be returned (according to the token).\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "array",
              "items": {
                "type": "integer"
              }
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "order_by",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "The default sorting is by creation date (date_created). Another sorting option is by the date of assignment to a publication channel (date_channel_assigned).",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "default": "date_created",
              "enum": [
                "date_created",
                "date_channel_assigned"
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "include_inactive",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Requires a full_access token.\nIf you want the system to also return paused/old job ads, include this parameter with the value 1.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "default": false
            },
            "deprecated": true
          },
          {
            "name": "only_deleted",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Requires a full_access token.\nIf you want the system to return ONLY deleted job ads, use this parameter.\nAt this point, however, the system will return the payload only with the job_id parameter (payload: [{job_id:1234},{job_id:5678}]).\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "boolean",
              "default": false
            },
            "deprecated": true
          },
          {
            "name": "status",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Requires a full_access token.\nThe parameter behaves as a bitmask. 1 = active, 2 = inactive, 4 = draft, 8 = deleted.\nAll combinations are allowed except for deleted, which can only be displayed separately.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "default": 1
            },
            "deprecated": true
          },
          {
            "name": "activity_state",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Requires a full_access token.\nThe parameter filters positions based on whether they are active (1) or inactive (2).\nThe parameter is also a bitmask, so individual values can be summed and used together (allows filtering by multiple options at once).\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "default": 1,
              "enum": [
                1,
                2,
                3
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "access_state",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Requires a full_access token.\nThe parameter filters job ads based on the logic of open and closed positions.\nUnlike activity_state, individual values cannot be combined.\n",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "enum": [
                1,
                2,
                3,
                4,
                5
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "with_rewards",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Displays job ads that are linked to a referral reward.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer",
              "enum": [
                0,
                1
              ]
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "updated_from",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filtering by the date of the last job ad edit. Format YYYY-mm-dd HH:mm:ss",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date-time"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "updated_to",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "Filtering by the date of the last job ad edit. Format YYYY-mm-dd HH:mm:ss",
            "schema": {
              "type": "string",
              "format": "date-time"
            }
          }
        ],
