      "post": {
        "tags": [
          "Jobs"
        ],
        "summary": "Create new job",
        "description": "This call creates a new job advertisement and saves it as a draft. \nFor proper functionality, the job ad must then be completed manually directly in the ATS Recruitis.  \nIn the response after creating the draft, a link is also returned for its completion and publication within the ATS Recruitis.\n\n#### Warning\nIf you do not complete the publication in ATS Recruitis manually, the ad will remain only as a draft. \nIf you then attempt to perform operations with it via the API, such as \n[publishing to a channel](#tag/Jobs/paths/~1jobs~1{id}~1channel~1{channel_id}/put), \n[changing access_state](#tag/Jobs/paths/~1jobs~1{id}~1access_state~1{state}/put), etc., \nthe job ad may end up in an inconsistent state and cause issues in ATS Recruitis or on the used publication channels.\n\n#### Requirements\n\n* The call must include an authorization token.\n* New token type:\n    * The token must have the `api.position.write` permission.\n* Old token type:\n    * Token type: `full_access`: creating a job ad always requires full access.\n",
        "requestBody": {
          "content": {
            "application/json": {
              "schema": {
                "type": "object",
                "properties": {
                  "title": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "Test job"
                  },
                  "description": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "Short description"
                  },
                  "text_language": {
                    "type": "string",
                    "example": "cs",
                    "enum": [
                      "cs",
                      "sk",
                      "en",
                      "de",
                      "ro",
                      "bg",
                      "hu",
                      "pl"
                    ]
                  },
                  "author_id": {
                    "type": "integer",
                    "nullable": true
                  }
                },
                "required": [
                  "title",
                  "description"
                ]
              }
            }
          }
        },
        "responses": {
          "201": {
            "description": "Job was created.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "payload": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "id": {
                          "type": "integer",
                          "example": 12345
                        }
                      }
                    },
                    "meta": {
                      "type": "object",
                      "properties": {
                        "duration": {
                          "type": "integer",
                          "example": 60
                        },
                        "total_duration": {
                          "type": "integer",
                          "example": 150
                        },
                        "code": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "api.created"
                        },
                        "message": {
                          "type": "string",
                          "example": "Job was created."
                        }
                      }
                    }
                  }
                }
              }
            }
          },
          "400": {
            "$ref": "#/components/responses/Response400"
          }
        }
      }
    },
    "/jobs/{id}": {
      "get": {
        "tags": [
          "Jobs"
        ],
        "summary": "Get job detail",
        "description": "Returns the details of a single job advertisement. The parameters in the response are the same \nas when multiple job ads are returned at once. You must take into account that individual \narguments may also be returned as null instead of a string or object.\n\nIf the given job ad does not exist, HTTP status `404` is returned with meta code `api.error.not_found`.\n\n#### Requirements\n\n* The call must include an authorization token.\n* Compatible with the company token.\n* New token type:\n    * The token must have the `api.position.read` permission.\n* Old token types:\n    * Token type: `public_access`: if it is a public job ad (published on company websites, XML, or job portals).\n    * Token type: `full_access`: if it is an internal job ad.\n\n#### Attribute active\n\nThe `active` attribute in the job ad listing indicates whether the given job ad is active, \ni.e., currently published somewhere and not paused.  \n\n* If the filter parameter `channel_id` is specified, then the `active` attribute indicates \n  whether the job ad is active in that specific publication channel.\n* If the filter parameter `channel_id` contains multiple channels, then the `active` attribute \n  is true if the job ad is active in at least one of the specified channels.\n* If the filter parameter `channel_id` is *not* specified, then the `active` attribute indicates \n  whether the job ad is active in at least one of all publication channels (i.e., it is currently \n  published *anywhere*).\n",
        "parameters": [
          {
            "name": "id",
            "in": "path",
            "required": true,
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "with_automation",
            "in": "query",
            "description": "If with_automation=1 is specified, the result of the call will also include a new field automations.",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "activity_state",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          },
          {
            "name": "access_state",
            "in": "query",
            "schema": {
              "type": "integer"
            }
          }
        ],
        "responses": {
          "200": {
            "description": "Job was found.",
            "content": {
              "application/json": {
                "schema": {
                  "type": "object",
                  "properties": {
                    "payload": {
